Title:          get_mplayer.tcz
Description:    Script to wget and compile MPlayer (movie player).
Version:        201612
Author:         nitram
Original-site:  n/a
Copying-policy: http://unlicense.org
Size:		100K
Extension_by:   nitram
Tags:           get mplayer compile command line multi media movie player
Comments:       -Run 'get_mplayer.sh' to wget and compile MPlayer with
                 FFmpeg to create an mplayer_custom.tcz extension.
                -MPlayer ./configure uses hardware autodetect, compile
                 natively on target system for best performance.
                -CLI, OSD and gmplayer (graphic) MPlayer compile options.
                -Default compile lean with Xorg, Alsa and libXv support.
                -Default options tested to compile and play well in TC7.
                -Prompted for additional configure options before compile.
                -Prompted to add extension to onboot.lst or OnDemand.
                -Prompted to create config and copy example configs.
                -Prompted to install default skin (gmplayer).
                -MPlayer is a command line multimedia player, uses
                 GPL2 license: http://www.mplayerhq.hu/design7/news.html
                -Thanks to Michael Zeising for the 'Productive' skin:
                 http://www.mplayerhq.hu/images/skins/productive-01.jpg
